274
00:22:56,800 --> 00:23:01,880
The platforms go through what democracy went through too long ago on limits.

275
00:23:02,040 --> 00:23:08,120
They are experimenting with it now but do not want to listen to anyone else, so that's a problem.

276
00:23:08,280 --> 00:23:11,120
Do you want to jump into the discussion?

277
00:23:11,280 --> 00:23:16,520
We who are engaged in the direct artistic activity often have a self -image -

278
00:23:16,680 --> 00:23:21,520
–This our institutions where the art is done in a way is unusual -

279
00:23:21,680 --> 00:23:25,640
- Of the freedom of speech and border problems.

280
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:30,160
We can no longer take that for granted in any way.

281
00:23:30,320 --> 00:23:37,520
We must think about how we can professionalize the part of the institutions -

282
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:42,960
– Or the parts of the art -practicing side -

283
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:46,040
- Which receives the political assignments.

284
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:51,720
We talk a lot about political governance, but often forget the intermediary.

285
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:56,080
There is a political governance, and then hand over to some -

286
00:23:56,240 --> 00:23:59,880
- As either distributes the money or does the art.

287
00:24:00,040 --> 00:24:05,560
We also have a tendency to get stuck in the contradiction -

288
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:10,160
