00:25:27,080 --> 00:25:31,640
Borders are crucial for artistic freedom to prevail.

305
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:39,240
Those limits should in some way formulate the principles, agreements -

306
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:46,680
- And other things that many people in artistic practice often find boring.

307
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:49,080
Policies and stuff.

308
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:54,600
Because if we cannot defend human rights within the institutions -

309
00:25:54,760 --> 00:26:00,760
- And we can't really today, then we can't expect to be able to keep the art free.

310
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:05,800
I led a media investigation recently -

311
00:26:05,960 --> 00:26:11,280
- Where we had with the democracy requirement and what you are in, and that is a combustible issue.

312
00:26:11,440 --> 00:26:15,880
Those standing on the freedom of speech-fundamentalist side-

313
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:20,400
- I think that this is an intervention and that the limit is too narrow.

314
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:26,440
I want to say two things.
 One is that you have become aware of how fragile the system is.

315
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:30,520
How easy it is to change for those who want to change it.

316
00:26:30,680 --> 00:26:36,560
But also what you are in with social media -

317
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:40,360
- As you can love on the one hand, but hate just as much.

318
00:26:40,520 --> 00:26:45,400
There are no democratic structures -

319
00:26:45,560 --> 00:26:51,040
- This means that we get to know what it is we are not told and who is stopped.

320
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:55,960
When Facebook is editor of what is written on Facebook -

321
00:26:56,120 --> 00:26:58,720
- I'll be dark scared.

322
00:26:58,880 --> 00:27:03,080
There, anything can come in and start controlling it.

323
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:06,960
We see today as I do in my naivety -

324
00:27:07,120 --> 00:27:11,840
- Near did not think could occur.

325
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:15,920
The second, that Carolina takes up ...

326
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:21,600
Who has said that in the production of art should not advise -

327
00:27:21,760 --> 00:27:24,920
—The common decency; human rights -

328
00:27:25,080 --> 00:27:29,720
- Jimination and respect?

329
00:27:29,880 --> 00:27:34,720
Then I have to say that what the art does, I shit in that.

